      <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In the error list of FitzPatrick’s <em>Advanced Calculus</em>, it’s said that
on p. 479, ln. 14–21, “it doesn’t seem that <script type="math/tex">\vect{P}_k</script> can be
chosen as indicated…”  I spent some time to understand what
<script type="math/tex">\vect{P}^*_k</script> was.</p>

<p>It took me an hour to see what’s wrong with <script type="math/tex">\vect{P}_k</script>.  It’s
<em>much</em> easier to understand the words using figures.</p>

<!-- more -->

<h2 id="what-the-vectjs-are">What the <script type="math/tex">\vect{J}</script>’s are?</h2>

<p>Suppose <script type="math/tex">\vect{I} \equiv [0,2] \times [0,2]</script>.</p>

<p><img src="/images/posts/Fitz479/partition1.svg" width="500" title="What the J’s are?" ><br />
<small><a href="/downloads/code/partition1.tex">Source code</a></small></p>

<p><script type="math/tex">\vect{J}</script> is any of the small rectangles in the above figure inside
<script type="math/tex">\vect{I}</script>.</p>

<h2 id="understanding-vectpk-vectj">Understanding <script type="math/tex">\vect{P}_k (\vect{J})</script></h2>

<p><img src="/images/posts/Fitz479/partition2.svg" width="500" title="What the P_k (J)’s are?" ><br />
<small><a href="/downloads/code/partition2.tex">Source code</a></small></p>

<p><script type="math/tex">\vect{P}_k (\vect{J})</script> is a partition of <script type="math/tex">\vect{J}</script>.  In other
words, <script type="math/tex">\vect{P}_k (\vect{J})</script> contains a small black solid square
and the gray dashed lines inside the square.</p>

<p>The above figure <em>can’t</em> be a partition of <script type="math/tex">\vect{I}</script>.</p>

<h2 id="understanding-vectpk-vectj-1">Understanding <script type="math/tex">\vect{P}^*_k (\vect{J})</script></h2>

<p><img src="/images/posts/Fitz479/partition3.svg" width="500" title="What the P^*_k (J)’s are?" ><br />
<small><a href="/downloads/code/partition3.tex">Source code</a></small></p>

<p><script type="math/tex">\vect{P}^*_k (\vect{J})</script> is a refinement of <script type="math/tex">\vect{J}</script>.</p>

]]></content>
    
